@Steve L

Streaming has radically changed music delivery.  Having huge streaming libraries available on a second’s notice without having to store albums or cds is fantastically convenient. Unfortunately the sonic quality suffers.  Everything is a trade off.  

I sold my vinyl LPs to a  local vinyl record store.  I hadn’t owned a turntable since the late 80s when mine was taken in a burglary, but had held onto the LPs for sentimental reasons.  I actually got a fair price.  My advice is to identify things like the Beatles, Dylan, the Who, Stevie Wonder etc. and negotiate prices for those separately.  It still feels weird not to have them

