I see from other comments that there is a legitimate argument for calling it a pun, but seeing a term lose its specificity bothers me, too. It tends to happen when people infer meanings from context, and it blunts the precision of the language. It can be argued that it's a natural and inevitable process, but so's aging, rust and rot. I don't feel obligated to be happy about it.

